'''Electrocar, Electrocart''' is an [[electric vehicle]], typically a small [[cart]] with an electrical driving gear and a [[storage battery]].
In the United Kingdom, similar small electric vehicles were known as electric drays.
A typical [[Soviet Union|Soviet]]/[[Belarus]]ian electrocar EC-1.00 (and also its modifications, including EC-1.00-1 designed and manufactured ({{As of|2007|lc=on}}) at [[Mogilev]] Automobile Plant ([[MoAZ]]) is frequently used in factories for the transportation of not so heavy loads, because it does not emit harmful [[exhaust gas|exhaust]]. {{-}}
