The '''Eolica Beidaud Wind Farm''' is a proposed wind power project in [[Beidaud]], [[Tulcea County]], [[Romania]]. It will consist of four individual wind farms connected together. It will have 64 individual [[wind turbine]]s<ref>[http://www.edch.ch/projects/descriptions.shtml Eolica Dobrogea to build wind farms in the Dobrogea region] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090210014204/http://edch.ch/projects/descriptions.shtml |date=2009-02-10 }}</ref> with a nominal output of around 2 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] which will deliver up to 128 MW of power, enough to power over 75,800 homes, with a capital investment required of approximately US$150 million.

