'''Silje Ask Lundberg''' (born 13 April 1988 in [[Oslo]]) is a Norwegian [[environmentalism|environmentalist]] and chairman of [[Norwegian Society for the Conservation of Nature]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://naturvernforbundet.no/nyheter/silje-ask-lundberg-valgt-som-leder-article36499-165.html|title=Silje Ask Lundberg valgt som leder|work=naturvernforbundet.no|access-date=2018-01-08|language=no-NO}}</ref> (Friends of the Earth Norway). She is a former leder of [[Nature and Youth]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Executive Committee of Nature and Youth 2013 |url=http://nu.no/ss/ |work=Nature and Youth |language=Norwegian |accessdate=3 October 2013 }}</ref>. She grew up in [[Harstad]] in Northern Norway. Prior to her leadership she has been deputy chairman and been working for other environmental organisations, such as [[Zero Emission Resource Organisation|ZERO]] and [[Bellona Foundation]].

