{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Wintergreen'' (book)}}
'''''Wintergreen''''', written in 1987, is a book by [[Robert Michael Pyle]].  It describes the devastation caused by unrestrained logging in [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]]'s [[Willapa Hills]].  It was also the winner of the [[John Burroughs]] [[Medal for Distinguished Nature Writing]].

